This is a proposal to amend the installation instruction for the mySQL setup & installation.

The setup of the mySQL DB is well described at
http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Setting+up+JIRA+Standalone+and+MySQL+on+Linux

What is missing is an option required for a dump of the DB.
These options - added by my later - were:
GRANT UPDATE on jiradb.* TO 'jirauser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
GRANT LOCK TABLES on jiradb.* TO 'jirauser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

The dump is done with a script like:
mysqldump --host=localhost --add-drop-table -v --user=jirauser --password=.... jiradb > $TEMPDIR/$JIRADUMP
{quote}

